135 void PropertyItem::onChange()
136 {
137  if (hasExpression()) {
138  for (auto child : std::as_const(childItems)) {
139  if (child && child->hasExpression()) {
140  child->setExpression(std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>());
141  }
142  }
143  for (auto item = parentItem; item; item = item->parentItem) {
144  if (item->hasExpression()) {
145  item->setExpression(std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>());
146  }
147  }
148  }

162 void PropertyItem::setPropertyData(const std::vector<App::Property*>& items)
163 {
164  // if we have a single property we can bind it for expression handling
165  if (items.size() == 1) {
166  const App::Property& prop = *items.front();
167 
168  try {
169  // Check for 'DocumentObject' as parent because otherwise 'ObjectIdentifier' raises an
170  // exception
171  auto* docObj = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<App::DocumentObject>(prop.getContainer());
172  if (docObj && !docObj->isReadOnly(&prop)) {
173  App::ObjectIdentifier id(prop);
174  std::vector<App::ObjectIdentifier> paths;
175  prop.getPaths(paths);
176 
177  // there may be no paths available in this property (for example an empty constraint
178  // list)
179  if (id.getProperty() && !paths.empty()) {
180  bind(id);
181  }
182  }
183  }
184  // it may happen that setting properties is not possible
185  catch (...) {
186  }
187  }
188 
189  propertyItems = items;
190  updateData();
191  this->initialize();
192 }
193 
194 void PropertyItem::updateData()
195 {
196  bool ro = true;
197  for (auto it : propertyItems) {
198  App::PropertyContainer* parent = it->getContainer();
199  if (parent) {
200  ro &= (parent->isReadOnly(it) || it->testStatus(App::Property::ReadOnly));
201  }
202  }
203  this->setReadOnly(ro);
204 }

397 QString PropertyItem::asSequence(const Py::Object& pyobj) const
398 {
399  std::ostringstream ss;
400  ss << '[';
401  Py::Sequence seq(pyobj);
402  bool first = true;
403  Py_ssize_t i = 0;
404  for (i = 0; i < 2 && i < seq.size(); ++i) {
405  if (first) {
406  first = false;
407  }
408  else {
409  ss << ", ";
410  }
411  ss << Py::Object(seq[i]).as_string();
412  }
413 
414  if (i < seq.size()) {
415  ss << "...";
416  }
417  ss << ']';
418  return QString::fromUtf8(ss.str().c_str());
419 }
420 
421 QString PropertyItem::asMapping(const Py::Object& pyobj) const
422 {
423  std::ostringstream ss;
424  ss << '{';
425  Py::Mapping map(pyobj);
426  bool first = true;
427  auto it = map.begin();
428  for (int i = 0; i < 2 && it != map.end(); ++it, ++i) {
429  if (first) {
430  first = false;
431  }
432  else {
433  ss << ", ";
434  }
435  const auto& v = *it;
436  ss << Py::Object(v.first).as_string() << ':' << Py::Object(v.second).as_string();
437  }
438 
439  if (it != map.end()) {
440  ss << "...";
441  }
442  ss << '}';
443  return QString::fromUtf8(ss.str().c_str());
444 }

461 QVariant PropertyItem::toString(const QVariant& prop) const
462 {
463  if (prop != QVariant() || propertyItems.size() != 1) {
464  return prop;
465  }
466 
467  std::ostringstream ss;
468  Base::PyGILStateLocker lock;
469  try {
470  Py::Object pyobj(propertyItems[0]->getPyObject(), true);
471  return toString(pyobj);
472  }
473  catch (Py::Exception&) {
474  Base::PyException e;
475  ss.str("");
476  ss << "ERR: " << e.what();
477  }
478  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
479  ss.str("");
480  ss << "ERR: " << e.what();
481  }
482  catch (std::exception& e) {
483  ss.str("");
484  ss << "ERR: " << e.what();
485  }
486  catch (...) {
487  ss.str("");
488  ss << "ERR!";
489  }
490 
491  return {QString::fromUtf8(ss.str().c_str())};
492 }

569 void PropertyItem::setPropertyName(const QString& name, const QString& realName)
570 {
571  if (realName.size()) {
572  propName = realName;
573  }
574  else {
575  propName = name;
576  }
577 
578  setObjectName(propName);
579 
580  QString display;
581  bool upper = false;
582  for (auto&& i : name) {
583  if (i.isUpper() && !display.isEmpty()) {
584  // if there is a sequence of capital letters do not insert spaces
585  if (!upper) {
586  QChar last = display.at(display.length() - 1);
587  if (!last.isSpace()) {
588  display += QLatin1String(" ");
589  }
590  }
591  }
592  upper = i.isUpper();
593  display += i;
594  }
595 
596  propName = display;
597 
598  QString str = QApplication::translate("App::Property", propName.toUtf8());
599  displayText = str;
600 }

602 void PropertyItem::setPropertyValue(const std::string& value)
603 {
604  // Construct command for property assignment in one go, in case of any
605  // intermediate changes caused by property change that may potentially
606  // invalidate the current property array.
607  std::ostringstream ss;
608  for (auto prop : propertyItems) {
609  App::PropertyContainer* parent = prop->getContainer();
610  if (!parent || parent->isReadOnly(prop) || prop->testStatus(App::Property::ReadOnly)) {
611  continue;
612  }
613 
614  if (parent->isDerivedFrom(App::Document::getClassTypeId())) {
615  auto doc = static_cast<App::Document*>(parent);
616  ss << "FreeCAD.getDocument('" << doc->getName() << "').";
617  }
618  else if (parent->isDerivedFrom(App::DocumentObject::getClassTypeId())) {
619  auto obj = static_cast<App::DocumentObject*>(parent);
620  App::Document* doc = obj->getDocument();
621  ss << "FreeCAD.getDocument('" << doc->getName() << "').getObject('"
622  << obj->getNameInDocument() << "').";
623  }
624  else if (parent->isDerivedFrom(ViewProviderDocumentObject::getClassTypeId())) {
625  App::DocumentObject* obj =
626  static_cast<ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(parent)->getObject();
627  App::Document* doc = obj->getDocument();
628  ss << "FreeCADGui.getDocument('" << doc->getName() << "').getObject('"
629  << obj->getNameInDocument() << "').";
630  }
631  else {
632  continue;
633  }
634 
635  ss << parent->getPropertyPrefix() << prop->getName() << " = " << value << '\n';
636  }
637 
638  std::string cmd = ss.str();
639  if (cmd.empty()) {
640  return;
641  }
642 
643  try {
644  Gui::Command::runCommand(Gui::Command::App, cmd.c_str());
645  }
646  catch (Base::PyException& e) {
647  e.ReportException();
648  Base::Console().Error("Stack Trace: %s\n", e.getStackTrace().c_str());
649  }
650  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
651  e.ReportException();
652  }
653  catch (...) {
654  Base::Console().Error("Unknown C++ exception in PropertyItem::setPropertyValue thrown\n");
655  }
656 }

663 QVariant PropertyItem::dataProperty(int role) const
664 {
665  if (role == Qt::ForegroundRole && linked) {
666  return QVariant::fromValue(QColor(0x20, 0xaa, 0x20)); // NOLINT
667  }
668 
669  if (role == Qt::BackgroundRole || role == Qt::ForegroundRole) {
670  if (PropertyView::showAll() && propertyItems.size() == 1
671  && propertyItems.front()->testStatus(App::Property::PropDynamic)
672  && !propertyItems.front()->testStatus(App::Property::LockDynamic)) {
673  return role == Qt::BackgroundRole
674  ? QVariant::fromValue(QColor(0xFF, 0xFF, 0x99)) // NOLINT
675  : QVariant::fromValue(QColor(0, 0, 0));
676  }
677  return {};
678  }
679  if (role == Qt::DisplayRole) {
680  return displayName();
681  }
682  // no properties set
683  if (propertyItems.empty()) {
684  return {};
685  }
686  if (role == Qt::ToolTipRole) {
687  QString type =
688  QString::fromLatin1("Type: %1\nName: %2")
689  .arg(QString::fromLatin1(propertyItems[0]->getTypeId().getName()), objectName());
690 
691  QString doc = PropertyItem::toolTip(propertyItems[0]).toString();
692  if (doc.isEmpty()) {
693  doc = toolTip(propertyItems[0]).toString();
694  }
695  if (doc.size()) {
696  return type + QLatin1String("\n\n") + doc;
697  }
698  return type;
699  }
700 
701  return {};
702 }
703 
704 QVariant PropertyItem::dataValue(int role) const
705 {
706  // no properties set
707  if (propertyItems.empty()) {
708  PropertyItem* parent = this->parent();
709  if (!parent || !parent->parent()) {
710  return {};
711  }
712  if (role == Qt::EditRole) {
713  return parent->property(qPrintable(objectName()));
714  }
715  if (role == Qt::DecorationRole) {
716  QVariant val = parent->property(qPrintable(objectName()));
717  return decoration(val);
718  }
719  if (role == Qt::DisplayRole) {
720  QVariant val = parent->property(qPrintable(objectName()));
721  return toString(val);
722  }
723  if (role == Qt::ForegroundRole) {
724  if (hasExpression()) {
725  return QVariant::fromValue(QApplication::palette().color(QPalette::Link));
726  }
727  return {};
728  }
729 
730  return {};
731  }
732  if (role == Qt::EditRole) {
733  return value(propertyItems[0]);
734  }
735  if (role == Qt::DecorationRole) {
736  return decoration(value(propertyItems[0]));
737  }
738  if (role == Qt::DisplayRole) {
739  return toString(value(propertyItems[0]));
740  }
741  if (role == Qt::ToolTipRole) {
742  return toolTip(propertyItems[0]);
743  }
744  if (role == Qt::ForegroundRole) {
745  if (hasExpression()) {
746  return QVariant::fromValue(QApplication::palette().color(QPalette::Link));
747  }
748  return {};
749  }
750 
751  return {};
752 }

764 bool PropertyItem::setData(const QVariant& value)
765 {
766  // This is the basic mechanism to set the value to
767  // a property and if no property is set for this item
768  // it delegates it to its parent which sets then the
769  // property or delegates again to its parent...
770  if (propertyItems.empty()) {
771  PropertyItem* parent = this->parent();
772  if (!parent || !parent->parent() || hasAnyExpression()) {
773  return false;
774  }
775 
776  parent->setProperty(qPrintable(objectName()), value);
777  return true;
778  }
779 
780  setValue(value);
781  return true;
782 }

1409 namespace Gui::PropertyEditor
1410 {
1411 class VectorLineEdit: public Gui::ExpLineEdit
1412 {
1413  int decimals;
1414 
1415 public:
1416  explicit VectorLineEdit(int decimals, QWidget* parent = nullptr, bool expressionOnly = false)
1417  : Gui::ExpLineEdit(parent, expressionOnly)
1418  , decimals(decimals)
1419  {}
1420 
1421  bool apply(const std::string& propName) override
1422  {
1423  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1424  if (!ExpressionBinding::apply(propName)) { // clazy:exclude=skipped-base-method
1425  QVariant data = property("coords");
1426  if (data.canConvert<Base::Vector3d>()) {
1427  const Base::Vector3d& value = data.value<Base::Vector3d>();
1428 
1429  QString str = QString::fromLatin1("(%1, %2, %3)")
1430  .arg(value.x, 0, 'f', decimals)
1431  .arg(value.y, 0, 'f', decimals)
1432  .arg(value.z, 0, 'f', decimals);
1433 
1434  Gui::Command::doCommand(Gui::Command::Doc,
1435  "%s = %s",
1436  propName.c_str(),
1437  str.toLatin1().constData());
1438  return true;
1439  }
1440  }
1441 
1442  return false;
1443  }
1444 };
1445 } // namespace Gui::PropertyEditor

2355 Base::Vector3d RotationHelper::getAxis() const
2356 {
2357  // We must store the rotation axis in a member because
2358  // if we read the value from the property we would always
2359  // get a normalized vector which makes it quite unhandy
2360  // to work with

2364 Base::Rotation RotationHelper::setAxis(const Base::Rotation& value, const Base::Vector3d& axis)
2365 {
2366  this->rot_axis = axis;
2367  Base::Rotation rot = value;
2368  Base::Vector3d dummy;
2369  double angle {};
2370  rot.getValue(dummy, angle);
2371  if (dummy * axis < 0.0) {
2372  angle = -angle;
2373  }
2374  rot.setValue(axis, angle);
2375  changed_value = true;
2376  return rot;
2377 }

2379 void RotationHelper::assignProperty(const Base::Rotation& value, double eps)
2380 {
2381  double angle {};
2382  Base::Vector3d dir;
2383  value.getRawValue(dir, angle);
2384  Base::Vector3d cross = this->rot_axis.Cross(dir);
2385  double len2 = cross.Sqr();
2386  if (angle != 0) {
2387  // vectors are not parallel
2388  if (len2 > eps) {
2389  this->rot_axis = dir;
2390  }
2391  // vectors point into opposite directions
2392  else if (this->rot_axis.Dot(dir) < 0) {
2393  this->rot_axis = -this->rot_axis;
2394  }
2395  }
2396  this->rot_angle = Base::toDegrees(angle);
2397 }

2458 void PropertyRotationItem::assignProperty(const App::Property* prop)
2459 {
2460  // Choose an adaptive epsilon to avoid changing the axis when they are considered to
2461  // be equal. See https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=24662&start=10
2462  double eps = std::pow(10.0, -2 * (decimals() + 1)); // NOLINT
2463  if (prop->isDerivedFrom<App::PropertyRotation>()) {
2464  const Base::Rotation& value = static_cast<const App::PropertyRotation*>(prop)->getValue();
2465  h.assignProperty(value, eps);
2466  }

2469 QVariant PropertyRotationItem::value(const App::Property* prop) const
2470 {
2471  assert(prop && prop->isDerivedFrom<App::PropertyRotation>());
2472 
2473  const Base::Rotation& value = static_cast<const App::PropertyRotation*>(prop)->getValue();
2474  double angle {};
2475  Base::Vector3d dir;
2476  value.getRawValue(dir, angle);
2477  if (!h.isAxisInitialized()) {
2478  if (m_a->hasExpression()) {
2479  QString str = m_a->expressionAsString();
2480  angle = str.toDouble();
2481  }
2482  else {
2483  angle = Base::toDegrees(angle);
2484  }
2485 
2486  PropertyItem* x = m_d->child(0);
2487  PropertyItem* y = m_d->child(1);
2488  PropertyItem* z = m_d->child(2);
2489  if (x->hasExpression()) {
2490  QString str = x->expressionAsString();
2491  dir.x = str.toDouble();
2492  }
2493  if (y->hasExpression()) {
2494  QString str = y->expressionAsString();
2495  dir.y = str.toDouble();
2496  }
2497  if (z->hasExpression()) {
2498  QString str = z->expressionAsString();
2499  dir.z = str.toDouble();
2500  }
2501  h.setValue(dir, angle);
2502  }
2503  return QVariant::fromValue<Base::Rotation>(value);
2504 }

2545 void PropertyRotationItem::setValue(const QVariant& value)
2546 {

2561  Base::UnitsApi::toNumber(axis.x, format),
2562  Base::UnitsApi::toNumber(axis.y, format),
2563  Base::UnitsApi::toNumber(axis.z, format),
2564  Base::UnitsApi::toNumber(angle, format));
2565  setPropertyValue(val);

3033 void EnumItem::populate(QMenu* menu)
3034 {
3035  if (!children || children->empty()) {
3036  auto action = menu->addAction(text);
3037  action->setData(fullText);
3038  return;
3039  }
3040  auto subMenu = menu->addMenu(text);
3041  for (auto& item : *children) {
3042  item.populate(subMenu);
3043  }
3044 }

3046 std::shared_ptr<EnumItems> getEnumItems(const QStringList& commonModes) // NOLINT
3047 {
3048  int index = -1;
3049  std::shared_ptr<EnumItems> enumItems;
3050  for (auto& mode : commonModes) {
3051  ++index;
3052  auto fields = mode.split(QStringLiteral("|"));
3053  if (!enumItems && fields.size() <= 1) {
3054  continue;
3055  }
3056  if (!enumItems) {
3057  enumItems = std::make_shared<EnumItems>();
3058  for (int i = 0; i < index; ++i) {
3059  enumItems->emplace_back(commonModes[i], mode);
3060  }
3061  }
3062  auto children = enumItems;
3063  int j = -1;
3064  for (auto& field : fields) {
3065  ++j;
3066  field = field.trimmed();
3067  auto it = children->end();
3068  if (field.isEmpty()) {
3069  if (!children->empty()) {
3070  --it;
3071  }
3072  else {
3073  continue;
3074  }
3075  }
3076  else {
3077  it = std::find_if(children->begin(),
3078  children->end(),
3079  [&field](const EnumItem& item) {
3080  return item.text == field;
3081  });
3082  if (it == children->end()) {
3083  it = children->emplace(children->end(), field, mode);
3084  }
3085  }
3086  if (j + 1 == (int)fields.size()) {
3087  break;
3088  }
3089  if (!it->children) {
3090  it->children = std::make_shared<EnumItems>();
3091  }
3092  children = it->children;
3093  }
3094  }
3095 
3096  return enumItems;
3097 }
3098
